criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Mechanical ventilation : invasive for at least 48 hours or non-invasive for at least
             24 hours, sequential or continuous

          -  Dyspnea ≥ 4 on a visual analogic scale (VAS) from 0 to 10

          -  Absence of delirium (evaluated by the CAM-ICU score) ;

          -  Communicative patient

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients on ECMO or decarboxylation ;

          -  Patients on long-term left ventricular support;

          -  Patients postoperatively following any surgery (pain from the procedure may interfere
             with dyspnea);

          -  Protected minors and adults;

          -  Pregnant women.
